text: Lol.  :) )     Blue box, white text over speech bubble ("TAGAROGU-go"  Tagalog)    Speech Bubble: (Japanese alphabet translation of P.I. PU-U-TAN INA above Filipino text. Text below underlines are specific one-to-one word translations "baishunpu" / prostitute for putang and "okaasan" / mother for ina.)    Blue box, white text, bottom left reads: ("FUiRIPIN DOuTERUTE Daitouryou" - Philippine President Duterte)    Orange text with arrow reads:  "Omae wa baishunpu no musuko da." Literally, "You (very rude / slangy Japanese) are a prostitute's son."

replies.text: I'm more surprised they're analyzing the swear word on what looks to be national television 6-o-clock news.    The facepalm embarrassment on the matter was already expected.  =/
On the bright side, I learned an unsavory Japanese words today which I never thought I'd read in Japanese mass media.  =/
